================================================================================
SECTION 1 — DEFINITIONS
================================================================================

"Specification" refers to the AXON Language Specification, including all
design documents, grammars, memory model descriptions, type system
definitions, AI-native compiler feature descriptions, and associated
materials published under the AXON project.

"Implementation" refers to any compiler, transpiler, interpreter, toolchain,
or runtime that implements the AXON language as defined in the Specification.

"Licensor" refers to Edison Lepiten, Founder and Project Director of AIEONYX.

"You" refers to any individual or organization accessing this Specification.

================================================================================
SECTION 2 — PERMITTED USES
================================================================================

You ARE permitted to:

  1. READ and study the Specification for personal educational purposes.

  2. CITE the Specification in academic papers, research, or technical
     writing, provided proper attribution is given:

       "AXON Language Specification v0.1, Ed / AIEONYX, April 2026.
        github.com/aieonyx/axon"

  3. DISCUSS, REVIEW, or CRITIQUE the Specification publicly, provided
     the origin and authorship are clearly stated.

  4. BUILD a personal, non-commercial prototype Implementation for the
     purpose of demonstrating feasibility or contributing to the AXON
     project, provided you notify the Licensor at github.com/aieonyx.

================================================================================
SECTION 3 — PROHIBITED USES
================================================================================

You ARE NOT permitted to:

  1. REPRODUCE the Specification in whole or in substantial part in any
     product, service, or publication without written permission.

  2. CREATE a competing programming language project that incorporates
     AXON's core design concepts — specifically:
       - AI-assisted deterministic ownership inference as a compiler pass
       - The three-mode memory model (AI-Inferred / Manual Hint / Raw Zone)
       - The @ai decorator namespace for compiler-level AI integration
       - The build-time AI audit trail architecture
     without explicit written license from the Licensor.

  3. CLAIM authorship or co-authorship of the Specification or its
     core concepts.

  4. USE the name "AXON", "AXON Language", or "AIEONYX AXON" for any
     competing project.

  5. SUBMIT the Specification or substantial portions thereof to any
     AI training dataset, model training pipeline, or data collection
     service without written permission.

================================================================================
SECTION 4 — PLANNED LICENSE TRANSITION
================================================================================

It is the intent of the Licensor to transition the AXON Specification and
reference Implementation to an open-source license (anticipated: Apache 2.0
or MIT) upon reaching a stable compiler milestone, expected no earlier than
the completion of Phase 4 of the development roadmap.

This transition will be announced publicly at github.com/aieonyx/axon.
Until that announcement, this License governs all use.

